This paper deals with computational geometry, specifically with the Delaunay triangulation of a set of points in the plane. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm described in the paper involves randomization, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also involves optimization, which could make it relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GR (Graphics).
